SYNOPSIS
========
   void receive_udp(string host, string msg, int hostport)

DESCRIPTION
===========
   Handle a received UDP message.

   This function is called for every message received on the UDP port. Usually
   it is passed on to some object that handles inter-mud communications.

HISTORY
=======
   - changed (3.2.1) -- added 'hostport' argument
   - changed (3.2.9) -- renamed to receive_udp() from receive_imp().

SEE ALSO
========
   send_udp(E), query_udp_port(E)
